{"id": "e68d3a85-f0ee-4902-8bf2-5be7afcdd39b", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T03:28:10.999867", "source": "agent", "thought": [{"cache_prompt": false, "type": "text", "text": "\n\n"}], "reasoning_content": null, "thinking_blocks": [], "responses_reasoning_item": null, "action": {"thought": "This is a complex task - I need to implement a Jinja-like template engine in Python. Let me break down what I need to build:\n\n1. **Environment class** - the central hub that owns:\n   - Loader (dict mapping template names to source strings)\n   - Compiled template cache\n   - Filter registry\n   - Test registry\n   - Global variables\n   - Autoescape policy\n   - Whitespace control (trim_blocks, lstrip_blocks)\n\n2. **Template class** - represents a compiled template:\n   - Parse source into AST\n   - Render with context\n   - Support standalone usage or bound to environment\n\n3. **Exceptions**:\n   - TemplateSyntaxError - for malformed templates\n   - TemplateNotFound - for missing templates\n\n4. **Features to implement**:\n   - Variables: `{{ name }}`, `{{ user.name }}`, `{{ d.key }}`\n   - Filters: `{{ name|upper }}`, `{{ missing|default(\"guest\") }}`\n   - Built-in filters: upper, lower, title, length, join, default, escape, safe\n   - Conditionals: `{% if %}...{% elif %}...{% else %}...{% endif %}`\n   - Tests: `is defined`, `is undefined`, `is odd`, `is even`, `is iterable`\n   - Comparisons: ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=, in, not in\n   - Loops: `{% for item in items %}...{% else %}...{% endfor %}`\n   - Scoped variables: `{% with label = \"draft\" %}...{% endwith %}`\n   - Blocks: `{% block title %}...{% endblock %}`\n   - Inheritance: `{% extends \"base.html\" %}`\n   - Includes: `{% include \"nav.html\" %}`\n   - Macros: `{% macro input(value) %}...{% endmacro %}`\n   - Imports: `{% import \"forms.html\" as forms %}`\n   - Undefined values: render as empty string, falsy in conditions\n   - Autoescape: HTML-escape when enabled, unless marked safe\n   - Whitespace trim: `{{-`, `-}}`, `{%-`, `-%}`\n\nThis is a significant implementation. I'll structure it as:\n1. Lexer - tokenize template source\n2. Parser - build AST from tokens\n3. AST nodes - represent different template constructs\n4. Compiler/Interpreter - render AST to output string\n5. Environment - manage templates, filters, tests, globals\n\nLet me start implementing this systematically.", "kind": "ThinkAction"}, "tool_name": "think", "tool_call_id": "019f0a8dbc23f3b3fcd76f82fa1730d5", "tool_call": {"id": "019f0a8dbc23f3b3fcd76f82fa1730d5", "responses_item_id": null, "name": "think", "arguments": "{\"summary\": \"Plan MiniJinja implementation\", \"thought\": \"This is a complex task - I need to implement a Jinja-like template engine in Python. Let me break down what I need to build:\\n\\n1. **Environment class** - the central hub that owns:\\n   - Loader (dict mapping template names to source strings)\\n   - Compiled template cache\\n   - Filter registry\\n   - Test registry\\n   - Global variables\\n   - Autoescape policy\\n   - Whitespace control (trim_blocks, lstrip_blocks)\\n\\n2. **Template class** - represents a compiled template:\\n   - Parse source into AST\\n   - Render with context\\n   - Support standalone usage or bound to environment\\n\\n3. **Exceptions**:\\n   - TemplateSyntaxError - for malformed templates\\n   - TemplateNotFound - for missing templates\\n\\n4. **Features to implement**:\\n   - Variables: `{{ name }}`, `{{ user.name }}`, `{{ d.key }}`\\n   - Filters: `{{ name|upper }}`, `{{ missing|default(\\\"guest\\\") }}`\\n   - Built-in filters: upper, lower, title, length, join, default, escape, safe\\n   - Conditionals: `{% if %}...{% elif %}...{% else %}...{% endif %}`\\n   - Tests: `is defined`, `is undefined`, `is odd`, `is even`, `is iterable`\\n   - Comparisons: ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=, in, not in\\n   - Loops: `{% for item in items %}...{% else %}...{% endfor %}`\\n   - Scoped variables: `{% with label = \\\"draft\\\" %}...{% endwith %}`\\n   - Blocks: `{% block title %}...{% endblock %}`\\n   - Inheritance: `{% extends \\\"base.html\\\" %}`\\n   - Includes: `{% include \\\"nav.html\\\" %}`\\n   - Macros: `{% macro input(value) %}...{% endmacro %}`\\n   - Imports: `{% import \\\"forms.html\\\" as forms %}`\\n   - Undefined values: render as empty string, falsy in conditions\\n   - Autoescape: HTML-escape when enabled, unless marked safe\\n   - Whitespace trim: `{{-`, `-}}`, `{%-`, `-%}`\\n\\nThis is a significant implementation. I'll structure it as:\\n1. Lexer - tokenize template source\\n2. Parser - build AST from tokens\\n3. AST nodes - represent different template constructs\\n4. Compiler/Interpreter - render AST to output string\\n5. Environment - manage templates, filters, tests, globals\\n\\nLet me start implementing this systematically.\"}", "origin": "completion"}, "llm_response_id": "019f0a8d8371e2c1b2fb82e190c7c92a", "security_risk": "UNKNOWN", "critic_result": null, "summary": "Plan MiniJinja implementation", "kind": "ActionEvent"}
